A vintage 1960s Japanese travel poster style illustration of a computer server room, with warm amber and teal tones. In the foreground, a retro CRT monitor displays an elegant Japanese wave pattern. Behind it, rows of massive mainframe computers with spinning tape reels stretch into the distance, their blinking lights creating a rhythmic pattern. A single office chair sits empty before the monitor, suggesting patient anticipation. Steam rises gently from a small ceramic teacup placed beside the keyboard. The scene is bathed in soft morning light streaming through venetian blinds, casting geometric shadows across the polished floor. The aesthetic blends mid-century modern design with subtle Japanese minimalism.
